# KMP Platform SDK — Overview

## Project identity
- **Type:** Kotlin Multiplatform **library (SDK)** meant to be added as a dependency to real applications.
- **Publishing:** Maven Central via `com.vanniktech.maven.publish`; versions are managed in the root `build.gradle.kts`.
- **Coordinates:** group `io.github.mudrichenkoevgeny`, artifact ids follow `kmp-platform-sdk-*` convention for published subprojects.

## Tech stack (high level)
- **Kotlin:** 2.x, coroutines, Kotlinx Serialization.
- **UI:** Compose Multiplatform (including `composeResources` + generated `Res`).
- **Architecture:** Decompose (component model).
- **Networking:** Ktor **client** (HTTP + WebSockets).
- **Serialization:** `kotlinx.serialization`, `FoundationJson` (shared foundation).
- **Security/storage (Android-first):** Android DataStore (encrypted settings abstraction), Google Tink.
- **Logging:** Kermit.
- **Platforms:** Android + WasmJs are enabled; iOS scaffolding exists but is currently commented out in Gradle.

## Repository layout
- **Root:** `settings.gradle.kts`, `build.gradle.kts`, `gradle/libs.versions.toml`.
- **Modules:**
  - `core/` — reusable building blocks and shared infrastructure used by features.
  - `feature/` — feature-specific capabilities.
  - `sample/` — reference host applications (wiring only).
  - `bom/` — version alignment for consumers.

## Module structure
### Core (`core/`)
- `core/` — reusable building blocks and shared infrastructure used by features.
- `core/common`
  - Network bootstrap (Ktor client + WebSocket service)
  - App error model and error parsing pipeline
  - Platform abstractions for encrypted settings storage
  - Common UI building blocks (e.g. loading/error components)
  - DI/wiring components (e.g. `CommonComponent`, network modules)
- `core/settings`
  - Global settings repository + storage implementations
  - Settings-related WebSocket message handling (when applicable)
- `core/security`
  - Security settings storage/repositories
  - Security-specific error parsing (`SecurityErrorParser`)
  - Token/password validation use cases (when applicable)

### Feature (`feature/`)
- `feature/user`
  - User auth/networking (`HttpClientConfigPlugin` implementations)
  - User settings/repositories + encrypted storage wrappers
  - User error model and parsing (`UserErrorParser`)
  - Use cases + Decompose screen components

### Other
- `sample/*`
  - Reference host apps: wiring `CommonComponent`/feature components, providing runtime `baseUrl`, registering error parsers, and registering WebSocket message handlers.
  - Treat sample as the source of truth for host integration.

## Boundaries (non-negotiable)
- `core/common` must not depend on feature modules (like `feature/user`).
- Feature modules depend on relevant `core/*` modules and shared foundation; they must not hardcode host app details.
- `sample/*` is for wiring only; do not move SDK/business logic into `sample/*`.
